## How AI Tools (ChatGPT etc.) Source High-Quality Car Images

> [!NOTE]
> ChatGPT and similar AI tools use a combination of approaches to show polished car images:
> 1. **DALL-E / Image Generation** — They generate images on-the-fly using their own image models. This guarantees a clean, studio-quality result but images aren't real photographs.
> 2. **Licensed Stock APIs** — Services like Getty, Shutterstock, or manufacturer press kits provide high-res, professionally-shot images.
> 3. **Curated CDNs** — Pre-processed, verified images hosted on fast CDNs (exactly what we're building with R2).

**For Velocity, the best realistic approach is:**
- Keep sourcing from Wikipedia/Wikimedia (free, extensive coverage of every car model)
- **Pre-download, optimize, and host on Cloudflare R2** so you own the images and they never break
- Use **AI verification** (already built with Gemini) to reject bad/wrong images at ingestion time
- Optionally supplement with **Google Custom Search Image API** (you already have API keys) for cars missing good Wikipedia photos

